    "what_description": "Serapias pseudocordigera is a species of orchid that belongs to the family Orchidaceae. It is a terrestrial orchid characterized by a short stem, 5-10 cm long, bearing 1-2 basal leaves, 1-2 x 0.5-1 cm, ovate-lanceolate, and a single, terminal, resupinate flower, 2-3 cm long, with a yellow-green, columnar labellum and a white or yellowish lip. The sepals are 2-3 x 1-2 mm, lanceolate, and yellow-green, while the petals are 2-3 x 0.5-1 mm, linear, and yellow-green. The plant flowers from April to June in the wild and is endemic to the Iberian Peninsula. It is a rare and endangered species due to its limited distribution and habitat degradation.",
